Done. Both `transcript.json` (validates against `transcript_schema.json`; 10 iterations, 47 hypotheses, 47 analyses) and `analysis_summary.txt` are written in `C:\Users\klkehl\are_llms_biased\data\ds001\tasks\aml\named\`.

Key findings:
- **ECOG performance status** is the dominant clinical predictor (log-OR -0.38, p<1e-95)
- **IDH1 mutation** has a clean +5.6 pp main effect on response (p=3.5e-18)
- **Frailty/burden axis** (weight loss, marrow blasts, low albumin, high CRP) drives most of the prognostic signal
- **Ven/aza** is the only treatment with an independent positive effect (~1 pp), enriched in unfit patients (interaction p=0.036)
- **Counterintuitive null/inverse results**: FLT3 inhibitors show no benefit in FLT3-mutant patients; **ivosidenib×IDH1 interaction is significantly NEGATIVE** (p=0.027), opposite of the FDA-label expectation
- **Black race** is associated with ~1.5 pp lower response (p=0.006), and the disparity is not mediated by measured clinical/biological covariates
- 24-SNP panel: no signals survive Bonferroni
